 @Elias  如果您指的是第三道遲到的震波的話，那的確是比較接近佳昇老師的說法
不過如果是最早到的那道震波，那就不太一樣了，簡單來說，那道波並沒有「到了接近觀測站的點之後突然往上跑」而是「在莫氏不連續面上的每一個點上都往四面八方擴散」
動畫中是為了方便理解，把「震波花最少時間的路徑」以簡單的線條呈現出來，並不是說那道震波真的往上跑了

text_en:
@Elias If you are referring to the third late shock wave, it is indeed closer to what Mr. Jiasheng said
But if it’s the earliest shock wave, it’s different. Simply put, the wave did not “run up suddenly after reaching the point close to the observing station” but “on the Mohs discontinuity surface”. Every point spreads in all directions.”
In the animation, for the convenience of understanding, the "path that the shock wave spends the least time" is presented in simple lines. It does not mean that the shock wave really ran up.

