 @LIS情境科學教材  我覺得厲害的是你們團隊，可以將這個麼多困難且複雜的知識內容修剪成大多數人一看就能輕易理解的簡易概念。再搭配科學家的故事，引導觀眾跟隨當代科學家們的腳步，去理解他們最初是用什麼樣的簡單想法一步一步地抽絲剝繭做科學。雖然只是一段小小的十來分鐘的故事影片製作，但這個中間過程一定花了很大的心力。我想我大概可以理解為什麼等待新一集的LIS故事需要那麼久的時間了。

你們的影片對我的學生來說大概就像是登山樓梯的第一階吧，也許跟他們所要面對的知識之山相比，在高度上或許是微不足道。但若沒有這個第一階，大概也不會有第一步了吧。

PS：我的學生當中，已經有班級拿你們的影片當作是中午吃飯時間的「配菜」了。希望這件事可以激勵你們繼續「成功」下去！

text_en:
@LISContext Science Textbook I think what is great is that your team can trim so much difficult and complicated knowledge content into simple concepts that most people can easily understand at a glance. Coupled with the stories of scientists, it guides the audience to follow in the footsteps of contemporary scientists and understand what simple ideas they used to make science step by step. Although it is only a small story film of ten minutes or so, a lot of effort must be spent in this intermediate process. I think I can probably understand why it takes so long to wait for the new episode of the LIS story.

Your film is probably like the first step of a climbing staircase to my students. It may be insignificant in height compared to the mountain of knowledge they are facing. But without this first order, there would probably not be a first step.

PS: Among my students, some classes have used your videos as "side dishes" for lunch time. Hope this event can inspire you to continue to "success"!

